FOLDER.DESCRIPTION: Shared folder for Rebates RCI Objects

MAPPLET.DESCRIPTION: This mapplet is used to summarize claims [from BCI]and lookup the hierarchy level names [from EDW]. This mapplet will be called for populating the missing rebateID and the regular CLNT_PRD_SUMM tables.
MAPPLET.NAME: mplt_Calc_CLNT_PRD_SUMM

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This takes the dispense date and puts it into a YYYYMM format for the output.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: DSPN_PRD_CD

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This lookup will return the CORP_CD based on the
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_CORP_CD

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: EXTL_LVL1_ID = EXTL_LVL1_ID_in AND EXTL_SRC_CD = EXTL_SRC_CD_in AND EFF_DT <= DSPN_DT_in AND EXP_DT >= DSPN_DT_in

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: LVL1_ACCT_ID = LVL1_ACCT_ID_in AND LVL2_ACCT_ID = LVL2_ACCT_ID_in AND LVL3_ACCT_ID = LVL3_ACCT_ID_in AND SRC_CD = PBMDW_SRC_CD_in AND REC_EFF_DT <= DSPN_DT_in AND REC_EXPRN_DT >= DSPN_DT_in

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Added as part of the 2010 Med-B project. These fields are not queried on the CLNT_PRD_SUMM tables, however, these tables feed CR, and these indicators are needed there. Values expected are 0/1, so select the MAX in case there are multiple records and one has value 1, another has value 0.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: MED_B_OPTIN_IND_out

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This will provide insight into what Rebate IDs have been assigned, and which ones are missing. Users can query the missing Rebate ID data that CAN BE FIXED, by pulling rows where the PRD_ID is HOLD. Any rows where the PRD_ID is populated with a monthly period, and the RBAT_ID = 0, then the claim has a non-fixable error on it and it is being processed w/o a Rebate ID.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: agg_Extnl_Lvl_Summary
